<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Book Notes</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="styles/style.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <div class="profile">
            <h1>Abhinav's <span style="color: red;">Notes</span></h1>
            <div class="web-intro">
                Welcome to my book notes collection! Here, I share my personal takeaways and insights from the books I've read across various genres.
                 These notes summarize key concepts, themes, and memorable lessons that stood out to me, offering a quick but insightful glimpse into each book.
                  Whether you're searching for a deeper understanding of a particular book or simply exploring new ideas, this collection is designed to provide thought-provoking summaries and reflections.
                 I hope these notes inspire you to dive into the books that resonate with you and explore new perspectives along the way!
            </div>
            <form action="/new" method="GET">
                <button type="submit" id="new">New Book</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="items">
        <%for(let item of noteItems){%>
            <form action="/notes" method="GET">
                <div class="item">
                    <div class="book_cover">
                        <img src="//covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/<%= item.cover_id %>-M.jpg"
                                srcset="//covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/<%= item.cover_id %>-L.jpg 2x" alt="Book cover">
                    </div>
                    <div class="book_content">
                        <p>Title: <%= item.title%></p>
                        <p>Author: <%= item.author%></p>
                        <p>Date Read: <%= item.date_read%></p>
                        <p>Rating: <%= item.rating%></p>
                    </div>
                    <input type="hidden" name="id" value="<%= item.id %>">
                </div>
            </form>
        <%}%>
    </div>
</body>
<script>
    // Attach click event to submit the form when the .item is clicked
    document.querySelectorAll('.item').forEach(item => {
        item.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
            this.closest('form').submit();
        });
    });
</script>
</html>